Length. 
<quantity id="10512EEA0618237F1A7A1F1FFE16C005" box="[315,469,799,826]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.625" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="6.75" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" unit="mm" value="7.625" valueMax="8.5" valueMin="6.75">6.75–8.5 mm</quantity>
(male), 
<quantity id="10512EEA0618237F19771F1FFD53C005" box="[566,656,799,826]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
(female).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D716830F0618237F1B9A1F5FFEB9C0A6" blockId="2.[166,1225,863,1050]" pageId="2" pageNumber="107">
C o m m e n t s. 
<bibRefCitation id="B338FEFE0618237F1AD71F5FFDB0C045" author="Linnavuori, R. E." box="[406,627,863,890]" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" pagination="17 - 56" refId="ref2834" refString="Linnavuori, R. E. 2007. Studies on the Miridae (Heteroptera) of Gilan and the adjacent provinces in northern Iran. II. List of species. Acta Entomologica Musei nationalis pragae, 47, 17 - 56." type="journal article" year="2007">Linnavuori (2007)</bibRefCitation>
has reported this species from 
<collectingRegion id="156D4DED0618237F1F461F5FFF3AC0A6" isEnumeration="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="107">Guilan, Tehran, Zanjan</collectingRegion>
provinces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D716830F0618237F1B9A1F9FFD73C725" blockId="2.[166,1225,863,1050]" pageId="2" pageNumber="107">
The species has been collected from a hilly steppes. It is a Anatolian species, known from Caucasus, 
<collectingCountry id="AFBEC39F0618237F1A271FC0FE59C0E5" box="[358,410,960,986]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="107">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="AFBEC39F0618237F1AE61FC0FE19C0E5" box="[423,474,960,986]" name="Iraq" pageId="2" pageNumber="107">Iraq</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="AFBEC39F0618237F1AA71FBFFDE2C0E6" box="[486,545,959,985]" name="Syria" pageId="2" pageNumber="107">Syria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="AFBEC39F0618237F191F1FBFFD70C0E6" box="[606,691,959,985]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="107">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B338FEFE0618237F19821FBFFC57C0E5" author="Linnavuori, R. E." box="[707,916,959,986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" pagination="17 - 56" refId="ref2834" refString="Linnavuori, R. E. 2007. Studies on the Miridae (Heteroptera) of Gilan and the adjacent provinces in northern Iran. II. List of species. Acta Entomologica Musei nationalis pragae, 47, 17 - 56." type="journal article" year="2007">Linnavuori, 2007</bibRefCitation>
). In the plant bug website (
<bibRefCitation id="B338FEFE0618237F1BEF1FDFFE80C0C5" author="Schuh, R. T." box="[174,323,991,1018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" refId="ref3090" refString="Schuh, R. T. 2014. On-line Systematic Catalog of Plant Bugs (Insecta: Heteroptera: Miridae). Retrieved April, 2014 from http: // research. amnh. org / pbi / catalog /" type="url" year="2014">Schuh, 2014</bibRefCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName id="10A9F88C0618237F1A131FE0FE2FC0C5" box="[338,492,992,1018]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E5DD5F1D0618237F1A131FE0FE07C0C5" box="[338,452,992,1018]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="107">Artemisia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="10A9F88C0618237F1ABA1FDFFDBDC0C5" box="[507,638,991,1018]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="10A9F88C0618237F19831FDFFC84C0C5" box="[706,839,991,1018]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Phlomis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E5DD5F1D0618237F19831FDFFCDCC0C6" box="[706,799,991,1017]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="107">Phlomis</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="10A9F88C0618237F18171FDFFC14C0C5" box="[854,983,991,1018]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lamiaceae</taxonomicName>
) have been reported as the hosts of species (
<bibRefCitation id="B338FEFE0618237F1AF21FFFFD60C725" author="Seidenstucker, G." box="[435,675,1023,1050]" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" pagination="119 - 129" refId="ref3061" refString="Seidenstucker, G. 1959. Heteroptera aus Anatolien II. Revue de la Faculte des Sciences de l'Universite d'Istanbul (B) 23: 119 - 129." type="journal article" year="1959">Seidenstucker, 1959</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
